      "id": "common-mistakes",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Common Mistakes to Avoid\n\n### 1. Infinite Loops\n```java\n// WRONG - i never changes!\nfor (int i = 0; i < 10; ) {\n    System.out.println(i);\n}\n\n// WRONG - condition never becomes false!\nint x = 1;\nwhile (x > 0) {\n    x++;  // x keeps increasing!\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Off-by-One Errors\n```java\n// Prints 1 to 9 (not 1 to 10!)\nfor (int i = 1; i < 10; i++) { }\n\n// Prints 1 to 10 (correct)\nfor (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) { }\n```\n\n### 3. Modifying Loop Variable Incorrectly\n```java\n// Confusing - don't modify i inside the loop\nfor (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {\n    i = i + 2;  // Unexpected behavior!\n}\n```",
