      "id": "summary",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Summary - What You Learned\n\nIn this part, you learned:\n\n- **`for` loop**: Best when you know the number of iterations\n- **`while` loop**: Best when you have a condition to check first\n- **`do-while` loop**: Best when code must run at least once\n- **`break`**: Exit loop immediately\n- **`continue`**: Skip to next iteration\n- **Nested loops**: Loops inside loops for 2D patterns\n\n## Key Points to Remember\n\n1. Always ensure loops can terminate (avoid infinite loops)\n2. Be careful with loop conditions (`<` vs `<=`)\n3. `for` is great for counting\n4. `while` is great for unknown iterations\n5. `do-while` guarantees at least one execution\n6. Nested loops multiply iterations (outer × inner)\n\n---\n\n### Next Up: Part 6 - Arrays\n\nLearn how to store and work with collections of data!",
